  "review": "This film is about a company called Nudge Inc. Their mission is to influence peoples decisions by using psychology techniques. The owner and founder of the company David Kahneman is interviewed throughout the film. His main premise is that humans are not logical beings and therefore should be influenced by simple nudges in order to make the correct decisions.br br Although this premise makes sense theoretically, in practice it does not work. While watching this documentary, I kept asking myself, Why don't the subjects realize that they are being manipulated? How would they ever know what is happening? After all, the Nudge team does not disclose their intentions when they create campaigns. Instead, they simply hope that the nudges will lead people in the right direction. For instance, a campaign designed to encourage people to contribute to charitable organizations. Rather than explicitly stating that people should donate, the nudge technique suggests donating to charities by rounding up purchases to the nearest dollar. Because people are unlikely to give exact amounts, they tend to round up to a larger amount, which increases donations."  
